;; CI perf-budget for the #44 propagation thesis — gated by experiments/propagation/check-budget.clj.
;; RATIO-based (machine-independent) + generous absolute ceilings, so CI timing noise does NOT flake.
;; Baseline (content-asserted, RESULTS.md §"Content-asserted"): graph-prop 1.6->2.2ms FLAT across
;; K=1..8; git-prop 49.9->313.7ms climbing (the merge-queue); graph-write ~175-210ms (eager index).
;; The two RATIO budgets encode the thesis directly and are immune to CI machine speed; the absolute
;; ceilings are catastrophe-catchers set ~10-20x above measured so noise never trips them.
{:sweep-ks "1,8"                         ; endpoints suffice: K=1 vs K=8 gives flatness + headline
 :graph-prop-flatness-ratio-max 4.0      ; graph-prop[maxK]/graph-prop[minK]; measured ~1.4 — the FLAT thesis (P1)
 :graph-beats-git-factor-min    8.0      ; git-prop[maxK]/graph-prop[maxK]; measured ~140x — the headline (P2)
 :graph-prop-abs-ceiling-ms     50.0     ; graph-prop[maxK] sanity ceiling; measured 2.2ms (very generous)
 :graph-write-abs-ceiling-ms    700.0    ; graph-write[maxK]; measured ~175-210ms (eager index; headroom for CI JIT)
 :require-no-lost-writes        true}    ; landed=K/K both arms — no write silently dropped
